fields.name: Never-Ending AI Codeverse (7-HR Hackathon)
fields.description:
A high-intensity hackathon where teams build innovative solutions using AI concepts and tools. Participants will ideate, design, and develop within a limited time frame. Creativity, technical skills, and problem-solving abilities are tested to the max.
Only the most resilient minds survive the codeverse.

fields.name: El’s AI Vision Lab(Prompt War)
fields.description: Participants generate images or videos using any AI tool based on a given theme. The challenge focuses on crafting powerful prompts that produce accurate and creative outputs. An AI-based evaluation system scores the submissions for relevance and quality.

fields.name: AI Logic from the Upside Down  (Coding Contest)
fields.description: An exciting coding contest filled with unexpected twists and logic challenges. Participants can code in any programming language of their choice. The event tests analytical thinking, adaptability, and coding fundamentals.

fields.name: Hawkins Data Decode
fields.description: Teams analyze a given dataset to uncover hidden patterns and meaningful insights. The focus is on data interpretation, visualization, and reporting accuracy. Logical reasoning and analytical thinking play a major role.

fields.name: Dungeons & Dragons(Board Game)
fields.description: A strategy-based board game where players navigate through fantasy scenarios. Quick decision-making and tactical thinking are key to survival. Each move determines the player’s fate in the game.

fields.name: Mind-Flayer Detects  (Guessing Game)
fields.description: A fun and fast-paced guessing game filled with twists and surprises. Participants must identify clues, patterns, or hidden connections accurately. Sharp observation and quick thinking are essential.

fields.name: Inter-Dimensional Insights  (Paper Presentation)
fields.description: Participants present research papers on topics related to AI, Data Science, or emerging technologies. Emphasis is placed on innovation, clarity, and presentation skills. Judging is based on content quality, originality, and delivery.

fields.name: Hawkins Premier League (IPL Auction)
fields.description:
Teams bid strategically to build their ultimate cricket squad within a fixed budget. Player selection, budget management, and team balance are crucial.
This event tests decision-making and teamwork skills.

fields.title: Inaugural Ceremony
fields.description: Opening ceremony with chief guest address and welcome speech

fields.title: Event Registrations & Brief
fields.description: Last minute registrations and event briefing for all participants

fields.title: Lunch Break
fields.description: Enjoy refreshments and networking with fellow participants

fields.title: Finals & Results Announcement
fields.description: Final rounds and announcement of winners

fields.title: Closing Ceremony
fields.description: Closing remarks, cultural performances, and dinner reception

fields.question: What is ARTIFA FEST?
fields.answer:
🎪 About ARTIFA FEST

ARTIFA FEST 2K26 is the ultimate intra-college symposium presented by the Department of Artificial Intelligence & Data Science.

"Where the Upside Down meets Innovation"

Step into the unknown, push your boundaries, and discover what lies beyond. This isn't just another symposium—it's an interdimensional experience where the mysterious "Upside Down" of Hawkins meets the cutting-edge world of Artificial Intelligence & Data Science.

Organized by the AI & DS Association, ARTIFA FEST bridges the gap between theoretical knowledge and practical application. From intense hackathons that test your coding prowess to non-technical events that challenge your creativity, every moment is designed to push you beyond your limits.

"Friends don't lie. Neither does good code." — The AI & DS Association

🔧 Technical Events at ARTIFA FEST

ARTIFA FEST features 6 exciting technical events that challenge your coding skills, problem-solving abilities, and technical knowledge in AI, Data Science, and programming.

🚀 Never-Ending AI Codeverse

7-Hour Hackathon

Team Size: 1-3 Members

Description: A high-intensity hackathon where teams build innovative solutions using AI concepts and tools. Participants will ideate, design, and develop within a limited time frame. Creativity, technical skills, and problem-solving abilities are tested to the max.

Skills Required: Programming, AI/ML concepts, problem-solving, teamwork

Duration: 7 hours (10:30 AM - 4:30 PM)

👁️ El's AI Vision Lab (Prompt War)

AI Image/Video Generation

Team Size: 1-2 Members

Description: Participants generate images or videos using any AI tool based on a given theme. The challenge focuses on crafting powerful prompts that produce accurate and creative results. Judges evaluate prompt engineering skills and artistic outcomes.

Skills Required: AI tool usage, prompt engineering, creativity, design sense

Duration: 6 hours (10:30 AM - 4:30 PM)

🔄 AI Logic from the Upside Down

Coding Contest

Team Size: Solo Event (1 Member)

Description: An exciting coding contest filled with unexpected twists and logic challenges. Participants can code in any programming language of their choice. The event tests analytical thinking, coding efficiency, and ability to handle complex logic puzzles.

Skills Required: Programming, logic, problem-solving, algorithm design

Duration: 6 hours (10:30 AM - 4:30 PM)

📊 Hawkins Data Decode

Data Science Competition

Team Size: 1-2 Members

Description: Teams analyze a given dataset to uncover hidden patterns and meaningful insights. The focus is on data interpretation, visualization, and reporting accuracy. Participants must present their findings and explain their analytical approach.

Skills Required: Data analysis, statistics, visualization, Python/R, presentation

Duration: 6 hours (10:30 AM - 4:30 PM)

🔍 Inter-Dimensional Insights

Paper Presentation

Team Size: 1-2 Members

Description: Participants present research papers on topics related to AI, Data Science, or emerging technologies. Emphasis is placed on innovation, clarity, and presentation skills. Judging is based on content quality, research depth, and delivery.

Skills Required: Research, technical writing, presentation, subject knowledge

Duration: 6 hours (10:30 AM - 4:30 PM)

🏏 Hawkins Premier League

IPL Auction

Team Size: 1-5 Members

Description: Teams bid strategically to build their ultimate cricket squad within a fixed budget. Player selection, budget management, and team balance are crucial. This event tests decision-making and teamwork skills in a cricket auction format.

Skills Required: Strategy, cricket knowledge, budget management, teamwork

Duration: 6 hours (10:30 AM - 4:30 PM)

  • Total Technical Events: 6
  • Team Events: 5 (Never-Ending AI Codeverse, El's AI Vision Lab, Hawkins Data Decode, Inter-Dimensional Insights, Hawkins Premier League)
  • Solo Events: 1 (AI Logic from the Upside Down)
  • Skills Covered: Programming, AI/ML, Data Science, Research, Strategy
  • Duration: 6-7 hours each

fields.question: How do I register for events?
fields.answer:
📝 How to Register for ARTIFA FEST Events

Follow these step-by-step instructions to register for your preferred events. The registration process is simple and user-friendly.

1

🌐 Access the Registration Portal

Navigate to the ARTIFA FEST website and click on the "Register" button in the navigation menu, or visit the registration page directly.

2

👤 Enter Your Personal Information

Fill in all required personal details accurately:

  • Registration Number: Your college registration number (required)
  • Full Name: As per your college records
  • Email Address: Active email for communication
  • Phone Number: Contact number for updates
  • Department: Your department name
  • Year of Study: Current year (I, II, III, IV)
3

🎯 Select Your Events

Choose events based on your interests and the registration rules:

  • Maximum 2 events per participant
  • ONE Technical Event + ONE Non-Technical Event
  • Cannot register for multiple events of the same category
Available Events:
🔧 Technical Events (6)
  • Never-Ending AI Codeverse (1-3 members)
  • El's AI Vision Lab (1-2 members)
  • AI Logic from the Upside Down (Solo)
  • Hawkins Data Decode (1-2 members)
  • Inter-Dimensional Insights (1-2 members)
  • Hawkins Premier League (1-5 members)
🎲 Non-Technical Events (2)
  • Dungeons & Dragons (Solo)
  • Mind-Flayer Detects (Solo)
4

👥 Team Formation (If Applicable)

For team events, follow these steps:

  1. Team Leader: One person creates the team
  2. Team Name: Choose a unique team name
  3. Team Members: Add member details if known
  4. Team Password: System generates a password
  5. Share Password: Share with team members for individual registration

Note: All team members must register individually using the team password

5

✅ Review and Submit

Before submitting:

  • Review all entered information for accuracy
  • Ensure event selection follows the rules
  • Check team details if applicable
  • Accept terms and conditions

Click the "Submit Registration" button to complete the process.

6

🎉 Confirmation

After successful registration:

  • You'll receive a confirmation email
  • SMS confirmation with registration details
  • Team password (if team event)
  • Registration ID for future reference
  • Further instructions and event guidelines

⏰ Registration Timeline

  • Registration Opens: January 15, 2026
  • Early Bird Discount: January 15 - January 31, 2026
  • Regular Registration: February 1 - February 5, 2026
  • Registration Closes: February 6, 2026 (11:59 PM)
  • Event Date: February 7, 2026

fields.question: What are the registration fees?
fields.answer:
💰 ARTIFA FEST Registration Fees

ARTIFA FEST offers affordable registration fees with early bird discounts. All fees are per participant and include access to selected events, refreshments, and participation certificates.

📋 Fee Structure

Early Bird Registration (Jan 15 - Jan 31, 2026) ₹150 per event
Regular Registration (Feb 1 - Feb 5, 2026) ₹200 per event
Spot Registration (Feb 7, 2026) ₹250 per event

💡 Fee Details

  • Per Event Basis: Fee is charged for each event you register for
  • Maximum Events: 2 events per participant (1 Technical + 1 Non-Technical)
  • Team Events: Each team member pays individually
  • Solo Events: Individual payment
  • Payment Methods: Online payment (UPI, Net Banking, Credit/Debit Cards)

🎁 What's Included in the Fee

✅ Included
  • Event participation
  • Participation certificate
  • Refreshments during event
  • Event materials
  • Access to workshops
  • Networking opportunities
❌ Not Included
  • Lunch/Dinner (available at campus cafeteria)
  • Travel expenses
  • Accommodation (if needed)
  • Personal expenses
  • Additional certificates

💳 Payment Information

  • Payment Gateway: Secure online payment system
  • Currency: Indian Rupees (INR)
  • Refund Policy: No refunds after successful registration
  • Payment Confirmation: Instant confirmation after successful payment
  • Receipt: Digital receipt sent via email

🎯 Special Discounts

  • Early Bird Discount: ₹50 off per event (Jan 15-31)
  • Group Discount: 10% off for teams of 3+ members
  • Student Discount: Additional ₹25 off for economically weaker sections (valid ID required)
  • Referral Discount: ₹25 off for each successful referral

🧮 Fee Calculation Examples

Example 1: Early Bird - 2 Events

Technical Event + Non-Technical Event = ₹150 + ₹150 = ₹300

Example 2: Regular - 1 Event

Single Technical Event = ₹200

Example 3: Team Event (3 members)

3 × ₹150 (early bird) - 10% group discount = ₹405

fields.question: How do I create or join a team?
fields.answer:
👥 Team Creation and Management Guide

For team events in ARTIFA FEST, proper team formation is essential. This guide will help you create a team or join an existing one.

🚀 Creating a New Team

1
Choose Team Event

Select a team event during registration:

  • Never-Ending AI Codeverse (1-3 members)
  • El's AI Vision Lab (1-2 members)
  • Hawkins Data Decode (1-2 members)
  • Inter-Dimensional Insights (1-2 members)
  • Hawkins Premier League (1-5 members)
2
Team Leader Registration

The team leader must register first:

  • Complete personal registration
  • Select the team event
  • Choose "Create New Team" option
  • Enter a unique team name
3
Generate Team Password

After team creation:

  • System generates a unique team password
  • Password is displayed on confirmation page
  • Save the password securely
  • Email/SMS contains team details
4
Share Team Information

Share with team members:

  • Team name
  • Team password
  • Event details
  • Registration deadline

🤝 Joining an Existing Team

1
Get Team Details

Obtain from team leader:

  • Team name
  • Team password
  • Event name
2
Individual Registration

Each member registers separately:

  • Complete personal details
  • Select the same team event
  • Choose "Join Existing Team" option
3
Enter Team Credentials

Provide team information:

  • Enter exact team name
  • Enter the team password
  • System verifies and adds you to team
4
Confirmation

After successful joining:

  • Receive confirmation email
  • Team member list updated
  • Payment completed individually

📋 Team Formation Rules

Team Size Limits
  • Never-Ending AI Codeverse: 1-3 members
  • El's AI Vision Lab: 1-2 members
  • Hawkins Data Decode: 1-2 members
  • Inter-Dimensional Insights: 1-2 members
  • Hawkins Premier League: 1-5 members
Important Guidelines
  • Minimum 1 member, maximum as per event rules
  • All members must be from same college
  • Each member pays registration fee individually
  • Team leader is responsible for coordination
  • Changes to team composition not allowed after registration deadline

💡 Team Management Tips

For Team Leaders
  • Communicate clearly with team members
  • Share password securely
  • Ensure all members register before deadline
  • Coordinate practice sessions
  • Keep backup contact information
For Team Members
  • Confirm team details before registering
  • Save confirmation emails
  • Stay in touch with team leader
  • Prepare for the event together
  • Arrive at venue on time

Wrong Team Password?

Contact your team leader to get the correct password

Team Full?

Check event capacity or create a new team
